There have been a great many philosophers who tried to understand the world through thoughts and observations. Here are some of the notable ones throughout time and the amount of publications they have made in shaping our world-view today.

Aristotle and Plato stand out as the giants of ancient philosophers who have made the most number of publications. Hegel stands out as the only modern philosopher who have made over 20000 publications.

There are common topics that the philosophers contemplated about.

Among the different topics, “analytic”, “german idealism”, and “continental” were the top 3 topics with the most number of publications. Note that Aristotle, Plato, and Nietzsche are not topics but appear on the plot due to a data quality issue.

The philosophical studies have fluctuated over time. It is not difficult to recognize the challenge of preserving and collecting published articles from ancient times. Therefore, the below plot shows the amount of philosophical publications over time since the year 1500.

The plot shows a clear trend in the increase of publications over time.

Analysis by Schools¶

Some topics remain a study of interest throughout time and others are short lived.

Aligning these publications with important historical events may bring insights as to why certain topics were popular at certain times. For example, “Feminism” first surfaced in the early 1800s and peaked in mid 1900s. This aligns with the women’s suffrage.

Other interesting observations can be made from a time series. For example, the below plot shows the contrasting relationship that capitalism has with communism.
